	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52194><span id= >Rexz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>182 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.55]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hey Luna, <br><br>Im not tryin to pick a fight with you but I thought you said youre not an expert on PLD?<br><br>Anyway, don't take my comment about &quot;What hybrid is the best soloer&quot; personally cause it was never meant against your post. I just happen to saw someone ask that question and decided to give my opinion based on my experiences.<br><br>To answer your post, here's a comparison between the two snares taken from Caster's Realm.<br><br>Shadow Knight's Dooming Darkness:<br>Casting time - 4.0 seconds<br>Mana usage&nbsp;&nbsp; - 120<br>Duration     - 1 minute 30 seconds<br>DoT          - 300 points<br><br>Ranger's Ensnare:<br>Casting time - 1.75 seconds<br>Mana usage   - 35<br>Duration     - 5 minutes<br>DoT          - none<br><br>Now let's take a testdrive on soloing battle field. If you ever tried to solo as a SK, you know you'll need to snare your mob more then once with dooming darkness. I've found that I've had to cast it 3 times on average until a mob is finally dead. So after killing a single mob, I've used up to 360 mana ( 3 casts x 120 mana ). By the time Im done killing two mobs in a roll, I just end up sitting and medding most of the time. In addition, whenever dooming darkness breaks due to it's short duration, the mob ends up running away at full spell with fear and it takes me 4.0 seconds to recast dooming darkness. Once in awhile, the mob gets too far away and I end up chasing it until fear breaks which isnt a lot of fun. <br><br>Whenever I soloed in the past with my ranger, I've never had any of these problems before. The ranger's ensnare is highly dependable. You just cast it once and forget about it. Best of all, you don't have much down time by having to meddi constantly.<br><br>As far as soloing Yeldevra in WW, he's a level 52 dragon. That's considered a monster type mob. If you need to know why rangers and pallies don't solo in WW it's because rangers can only fear animals and pallies can only fear undeads. Btw, don't get offended if I need to ask you this but don't you think a level 52 mob would be rather easy for a 60 SK? I was fear kiting ravishings in DL when my SK was 49 and the ravishings are level 45.<br><br>One other question I need to ask you is &quot;where did the issue of root come from?&quot; I never mentioned anywhere about rangers using root when snare-fearing mobs. What brought that up?<br><br>59th Ranger<br>51st Shadow Knight<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
