	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>311 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.76]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Heh--definitely NOT an expert on PLD/RGR or anything at all for that matter.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)  However, I have some 60 PLD friends that are reasonably strong and can solo really well.  Ive seen 'em do it.  Granted, the soloing Ive typically seen has been in Velks, Seb, FG, etc but I have seen, on a few occasions, a 60 PLD solo one of those damn Bulwarks (spl?) at the entrance to SG and those turds are a pain.  =)  I have yet to try, but I can assure you that fear-kiting wont be in my plans.  /smile (actually, that might be asolo situation where a PLD has an advantage over an SK or a RGR...)<br><br>Also, Im not making any conclusions at all about which class can solo the best.  I think that the answer is based on a lot of things.  <br><br>RGRs might have the best duration snare spell, but, in does that outweigh the damage that the SK snares do?  Im not sure.  Cascading is the best DoT (in terms of DPS, pre-pop also) that an SK gets.  When I fear-kite nowadays, say in ME, I generally only cast this once, fear (this will be several times) and only have to cast Engulfing once to finish him off.  I pull with cascading, and generally dump 2 Dots on him coming in, and then fear.  It works fairly well.  If I pulled with dooming, the fight would probably go longer, but its much less mana intensive, but I still generally dont; I like the damage from cascading.<br><br>I also was confused by you using the term &amp;#8220;break.&amp;#8221;  I think you mean that the spell duration has run its course and has worn off.  I generally interpret &amp;#8220;break&amp;#8221; as an interruption in the duration, prior to the spell duration running its course (i.e. fear fadin prior to the full duration, etc.)<br><br>As far as Yeldevra, that was only an example of one of the harder high level mobs that can be soloed by an SK (or NEC).  I don&amp;#8217;t know who the hardest is, but Yel has to be up there.  Is there a harder mob that a RGR or PLD can solo?  I don&amp;#8217;t know; don&amp;#8217;t play either of those classes.  =).  As far as being easy for a 60, heh, probably wouldn&amp;#8217;t go that far.  I have a 60 DE SK friend that was reasonably equipped fail the first couple of times he tried.  He a wimp for a group, but a decent to good challenge for a solo person.  A SK soloing a ravishing in DL is a far cry from an SK soloing Yeldevra in WW, even factoring in the level difference.<br><br>Root was only brought up as another way a RGR can solo.  I didn&amp;#8217;t really make too much a point of it; guess Im shocked you are asking about it.  =)<br><br>Also, I apologize if my message came across as attacking or anything.  If it did, I didn&amp;#8217;t effectively communicate.  I was merely challenging your statements, not saying they were right or wrong (for the most part), or anything else derogatory.  Just wanted clarification  =)<br><br>Luna</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
